help:python vertex;help:scripting vertex
These functions allows you to manipulate the vertices
leaving the topology unchanged or automatically recalculated.

gf.vertexAdd()
gf.vertexAdd(pos)
  Adds new vertex returning its index.
gf.vertexRemove(index)
  Removes vertex with the given index.
gf.vertexSetPos(index, pos)
  Sets the position of the vertex with given index.
gf.vertexGetPos(index)
  Returns the position of the vertex with given index.

gf.vertexSelect(index)
gf.vertexNext()
gf.vertexPrevious()
gf.vertexDeselect()
  Selects given/next/previous/none vertex.
gf.vertexSelected()
  Returns the index of the selected vertex.

gf.posRotate(pos)
  Transforms the coordinates according to the current figure rotation.
gf.posRotateBack(pos)
  Inverse of the previous function.

Position is always a tuple of length equal to the current number of dimensions.
